                             @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}


@{i}Installing the game@{ui}

The archive decompresses into its own drawer. Just copy or move the
drawer and its icon into whatever directory you want to keep it in. Sorry,
there's no install script yet, you really don't need one anyway.


@{i}Installing extra maps@{ui}

When you've got a new map you can install it by putting it into the maps
directory. The program will know if it's there. No more is needed to use
these extra maps. Just run the game, choose your new map and have fun.


@{i}Installing keyfile@{ui}

To install the keyfile, copy it into the battlecraft directory. From then
on you'll be able to use external maps and make savegames.
@EndNode
 

